00:00:41.174 --> 00:00:44.512 position:10% line:83% align:start
They say she's hypnotized Pas
with her seductive charms!

00:00:45.078 --> 00:00:47.582 position:5% line:83% align:start
[LICORICE] May I ask where it is
you're taking me, Pastry?

00:00:47.715 --> 00:00:49.984 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
A very special place.

00:00:50.117 --> 00:00:51.719 position:35% line:83% align:start
[LICORICE]
Sounds intriguing!

00:00:54.154 --> 00:00:57.792 position:19% line:83% align:start
Welcome to my workshop
of dreams!

00:00:57.926 --> 00:00:59.326 position:38% line:89% align:start
Oh, wow!

00:01:09.003 --> 00:01:11.506 position:13% line:83% align:start
[NARRATOR] This is the tale
of a genius patissier

00:01:11.639 --> 00:01:13.841 position:21% line:83% align:start
whose dream of making
the world's greatest dessert

00:01:13.975 --> 00:01:15.108 position:30% line:89% align:start
was cut short.

00:01:15.242 --> 00:01:17.011 position:27% line:83% align:start
Now, reincarnated
into another realm

00:01:17.144 --> 00:01:18.546 position:13% line:89% align:start
as the son of a poor noble,

00:01:18.680 --> 00:01:21.783 position:24% line:83% align:start
he pursues a world
full of desserts and smiles!

00:01:22.215 --> 00:01:25.485 position:13% line:83% align:start
A tale that's syrupy sweet,
chock full of yummy treats

00:01:25.620 --> 00:01:28.088 position:33% line:83% align:start
and sprinkled
with bitter darkness.

00:01:28.221 --> 00:01:30.992 position:30% line:83% align:start
A pastry chef,
who was reborn,

00:01:31.124 --> 00:01:32.259 position:19% line:89% align:start
and dreams of creating

00:01:32.392 --> 00:01:36.196 position:27% line:83% align:start
this new world's
very own land of sweets!

00:03:08.089 --> 00:03:11.092 position:13% line:83% align:start
[MALE ATTENDANT 1] My Lord,
are you certain of this?

00:03:11.592 --> 00:03:14.062 position:16% line:83% align:start
I understand your purpose
in sending Lady Petra

00:03:14.194 --> 00:03:15.630 position:10% line:89% align:start
to study in the royal capital

00:03:15.763 --> 00:03:18.365 position:13% line:83% align:start
was to strengthen the trust
of the Duke's family.

00:03:18.498 --> 00:03:20.333 position:21% line:83% align:start
But why did you send
Lady Licorice

00:03:20.467 --> 00:03:21.736 position:19% line:89% align:start
to the Fief of Morteln?

00:03:21.869 --> 00:03:24.204 position:19% line:83% align:start
I can't stand thinking
that sly woman

00:03:24.337 --> 00:03:26.040 position:24% line:83% align:start
is hatching schemes
behind my back

00:03:26.174 --> 00:03:28.009 position:10% line:89% align:start
as our house's fortune rises.

00:03:28.142 --> 00:03:30.978 position:13% line:83% align:start
[MALE ATTENDANT 1] I assume
you're referring to Count Retes?

00:03:31.112 --> 00:03:32.146 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yes.

00:03:32.680 --> 00:03:34.381 position:10% line:83% align:start
[HUBAREK] It's obvious enough
that she has designs

00:03:34.515 --> 00:03:37.618 position:16% line:83% align:start
on my future son-in-law,
is it not?

00:03:37.752 --> 00:03:39.153 position:24% line:83% align:start
[MALE ATTENDANT 1]
It is.

00:03:39.286 --> 00:03:41.956 position:16% line:83% align:start
A woman exemplary enough
to maintain such tight control

00:03:42.090 --> 00:03:45.425 position:7% line:83% align:start
of the south has surely grasped
the Fief of Morteln's potential.

00:03:45.560 --> 00:03:47.628 position:21% line:83% align:start
And all of a sudden,
she decides to invite him

00:03:47.762 --> 00:03:50.164 position:13% line:89% align:start
to a tea tasting ceremony?

00:03:50.297 --> 00:03:51.733 position:21% line:89% align:start
It's so transparent.

00:03:51.999 --> 00:03:53.400 position:35% line:89% align:start
I see now,

00:03:53.534 --> 00:03:55.335 position:24% line:83% align:start
with Lady Licorice
staying at the Morteln estate,

00:03:55.469 --> 00:03:59.073 position:7% line:83% align:start
it wouldn't be unusual for her
to accompany him to the party.

00:03:59.674 --> 00:04:01.809 position:21% line:83% align:start
Even for that vixen,
it would prove difficult

00:04:01.943 --> 00:04:04.512 position:19% line:83% align:start
to dote on Lord Pastry
too much with his fiancee

00:04:04.645 --> 00:04:06.413 position:16% line:89% align:start
right there at his side.

00:04:07.749 --> 00:04:08.482 position:41% line:89% align:start
[sighs]

00:04:08.616 --> 00:04:09.817 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HUBAREK]
And of course,

00:04:09.951 --> 00:04:11.953 position:33% line:83% align:start
it's probably
just fatherly instinct

00:04:12.086 --> 00:04:15.156 position:5% line:83% align:start
to want to make sure my daughter
is out of harm's way.

00:04:15.288 --> 00:04:16.256 position:24% line:83% align:start
[MALE ATTENDANT 1]
Are you worried

00:04:16.389 --> 00:04:17.525 position:7% line:89% align:start
about our neighbor, Lutoroute?

00:04:17.992 --> 00:04:20.494 position:7% line:83% align:start
I sincerely doubt they'll take
news of the engagement

00:04:20.628 --> 00:04:23.396 position:19% line:83% align:start
between the ducal house
and ours lying down.

00:04:24.832 --> 00:04:28.669 position:16% line:83% align:start
Amazing! I've never seen
such an enormous kitchen before!

00:04:28.803 --> 00:04:32.507 position:27% line:83% align:start
