Ow! That hurt!

00:09:43.552 --> 00:09:44.919 position:10% line:89% align:start
Oh, what are you doing here?

00:09:45.052 --> 00:09:46.687 position:10% line:89% align:start
Shouldn't I be the one asking

00:09:46.821 --> 00:09:48.189 position:19% line:83% align:start
why you're all gathered
at the door?

00:09:48.322 --> 00:09:50.691 position:16% line:89% align:start
What? Oh, um. I'm just...

00:09:50.825 --> 00:09:52.726 position:27% line:83% align:start
-You too, Mother?
-[laughs]

00:09:52.860 --> 00:09:54.628 position:10% line:89% align:start
I have business to attend to!

00:09:54.762 --> 00:09:56.130 position:35% line:83% align:start
[JOSEPHINE]
We should hurry up and get busy!

00:09:56.263 --> 00:09:58.466 position:27% line:83% align:start
[BOTH] Delighted
to see you again, Licorice!

00:09:58.599 --> 00:09:59.900 position:30% line:89% align:start
[ALL laughing]

00:10:00.034 --> 00:10:02.636 position:33% line:83% align:start
-Ah! My lady!
-Hey, Lady Josephine, wait!

00:10:02.770 --> 00:10:05.072 position:10% line:89% align:start
Eavesdropping's a bad habit.

00:10:05.206 --> 00:10:06.373 position:30% line:89% align:start
We were framed!

00:10:06.508 --> 00:10:07.842 position:38% line:89% align:start
Damn it!

00:10:07.975 --> 00:10:10.111 position:21% line:83% align:start
This is why you can't
ever trust grown-ups!

00:10:10.579 --> 00:10:11.779 position:21% line:89% align:start
[PAS] I was thinking

00:10:11.912 --> 00:10:13.881 position:27% line:83% align:start
of having you try
the candied bonkas, but--

00:10:14.014 --> 00:10:15.182 position:41% line:83% align:start
[LUMI]
Can we eat them?

00:10:15.316 --> 00:10:16.183 position:35% line:89% align:start
Heck, yeah!

00:10:16.317 --> 00:10:17.384 position:33% line:89% align:start
[BOTH grunt]

00:10:17.519 --> 00:10:19.153 position:44% line:89% align:start
What?

00:10:19.286 --> 00:10:21.422 position:13% line:83% align:start
As punishment for snooping,
you two will just have to wait.

00:10:21.556 --> 00:10:23.457 position:41% line:83% align:start
[BOTH]
Huh?

00:10:24.425 --> 00:10:26.460 position:38% line:83% align:start
I suppose
I can let Father and Feuille

00:10:26.595 --> 00:10:27.728 position:19% line:89% align:start
try them in your place.

00:10:27.862 --> 00:10:30.397 position:41% line:83% align:start
[BOTH]
Aw, man!

00:10:31.165 --> 00:10:32.766 position:38% line:89% align:start
[laughs]

00:10:34.301 --> 00:10:36.605 position:38% line:83% align:start
[FEUILLE]
I hope it'll be all right.

00:10:36.937 --> 00:10:38.772 position:21% line:89% align:start
Huh? What's this now?

00:10:39.006 --> 00:10:40.975 position:5% line:89% align:start
Well, it's about Pas' bodyguard.

00:10:41.108 --> 00:10:43.545 position:19% line:83% align:start
I don't think a newbie,
like, Nicolo can really handle

00:10:43.677 --> 00:10:44.945 position:27% line:89% align:start
a job like that.

00:10:45.079 --> 00:10:46.747 position:35% line:83% align:start
[CASSEROLE]
Count Retes' tea tasting parties

00:10:46.881 --> 00:10:48.149 position:16% line:89% align:start
are known to draw young,

00:10:48.282 --> 00:10:49.817 position:24% line:83% align:start
marriageable nobles
from all over the south.

00:10:49.950 --> 00:10:51.620 position:24% line:83% align:start
They're essentially
a social gathering

00:10:51.785 --> 00:10:53.154 position:27% line:89% align:start
for matchmaking.

00:10:53.287 --> 00:10:54.188 position:24% line:89% align:start
This kind of event

00:10:54.321 --> 00:10:55.789 position:30% line:83% align:start
is not intended
for either of us.

00:10:55.923 --> 00:10:57.358 position:24% line:89% align:start
I understand that,

00:10:57.491 --> 00:10:59.760 position:10% line:83% align:start
but this is still Count Retes
we're dealing with!

00:10:59.894 --> 00:11:03.430 position:19% line:83% align:start
True, but I know my son
can handle himself.

00:11:03.898 --> 00:11:06.433 position:21% line:83% align:start
I'm much more worried
about Lady Licorice.

00:11:07.168 --> 00:11:09.504 position:35% line:83% align:start
Of course,
Caera will be accompanying her,

00:11:09.638 --> 00:11:11.005 position:30% line:89% align:start
but I can't say

00:11:11.138 --> 00:11:12.806 position:21% line:83% align:start
she seems comfortable
with social situations.

00:11:13.340 --> 00:11:16.210 position:10% line:83% align:start
I hope that Vixen doesn't try
to embarrass her.

00:11:18.412 --> 00:11:21.015 position:16% line:89% align:start
I'm counting on you, Pas.

00:11:23.117 --> 00:11:26.521 position:16% line:89% align:start
[firecrackers crackling]

00:11:26.655 --> 00:11:28.889 position:50% line:89% align:start
âª

00:11:31.258 --> 00:11:32.893 position:38% line:83% align:start
[NICOLO]
Look at all these people!

00:11:33.027 --> 00:11:35.462 position:24% line:83% align:start
And the decorations
in the great hall.

00:11:35.597 --> 00:11:38.933 position:10% line:83% align:start
This is even more impressive
than the royal capital!

00:11:39.333 --> 00:11:40.301 position:38% line:89% align:start
Oh, wow.

00:11:40.434 --> 00:11:41.902 position:33% line:83% align:start
This is quite
an impressive room.

00:11:42.036 --> 00:11:43.538 position:13% line:89% align:start
Retesvale Castle is famous

00:11:43.672 --> 00:11:46.207 position:16% line:83% align:start
for being one of the most
prominent castles of the south.

00:11:46.340 --> 00:11:48.842 position:13% line:83% align:start
All the locals refer to it
as "Pirate Castle"

00:11:48.976 --> 00:11:51.312 position:16% line:83% align:start
being that it is settled
so close to the ocean.

00:11:51.646 --> 00:11:52.446 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm.

00:11:52.581 --> 00:11:54.315 position:30% line:89% align:start
Pirate Castle.

00:11:55.716 --> 00:11:57.051 position:35% line:83% align:start
[LICORICE]
Um, Pastry?

00:11:57.184 --> 00:11:59.286 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
Look at all these chandeliers.

00:11:59.787 --> 00:12:01.422 position:19% line:83% align:start
How many casks of sugar
could I buy

00:12:01.556 --> 00:12:04.091 position:21% line:83% align:start
with the money spent
on just one of them?

00:12:04.693 --> 00:12:05.594 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:12:05.726 --> 00:12:07.629 position:21% line:89% align:start
Oh! Um, it's nothing!

00:12:07.761 --> 00:12:09.129 position:41% line:83% align:start
[CAERA]
Lord Pastry,

00:12:09.531 --> 00:12:12.233 position:10% line:83% align:start
would you please keep in mind
that you are the lady's escort?

00:12:12.366 --> 00:12:14.735 position:30% line:83% align:start
Your attention
should be focused on her.

00:12:14.868 --> 00:12:16.370 position:24% line:89% align:start
Right. Forgive me.

00:12:16.504 --> 00:12:18.472 position:19% line:89% align:start
I'm so sorry, Licorice.

00:12:18.739 --> 00:12:20.207 position:24% line:89% align:start
That's kinda weird.

00:12:21.141 --> 00:12:22.142 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:12:22.276 --> 00:12:23.277 position:33% line:89% align:start
What's that?

00:12:23.410 --> 00:12:25.946 position:19% line:83% align:start
Isn't that the picture
I gave her?

00:12:27.314 --> 00:12:30.317 position:16% line:83% align:start
[PAS] I didn't expect her
to put it on full display.

00:12:31.218 --> 00:12:33.020 position:10% line:89% align:start
It almost feels intentional.

00:12:33.153 --> 00:12:34.288 position:38% line:83% align:start
[COATON]
Well, well!

00:12:34.421 --> 00:12:36.991 position:35% line:83% align:start
If it isn't
the Lord Pastry Morteln.

00:12:37.124 --> 00:12:39.460 position:27% line:83% align:start
We are so pleased
you could join us today.

00:12:40.361 --> 00:12:43.264 position:16% line:83% align:start
And I was greatly honored
to receive an invitation

00:12:43.397 --> 00:12:44.431 position:27% line:89% align:start
to today's event.

00:12:44.865 --> 00:12:45.966 position:35% line:89% align:start
Of course.

00:12:46.100 --> 00:12:47.434 position:19% line:83% align:start
Her Excellency asked me
to ensure

00:12:47.569 --> 00:12:49.638 position:30% line:83% align:start
you are treated
with only the utmost respect

00:12:49.770 --> 00:12:51.105 position:24% line:89% align:start
while you are here.

00:12:51.238 --> 00:12:53.173 position:21% line:83% align:start
Also, in the interest
of full transparency,

00:12:53.307 --> 00:12:55.976 position:24% line:83% align:start
I was told to keep
a close eye on you, as well.

00:12:56.410 --> 00:12:58.713 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
They think I'm a troublemaker.

00:12:58.846 --> 00:13:00.582 position:21% line:83% align:start
Right, let's keep up
the pretense

00:13:00.715 --> 00:13:01.849 position:13% line:89% align:start
for just a bit longer then!

00:13:01.982 --> 00:13:03.350 position:38% line:83% align:start
[COATON]
Most agreed.

00:13:03.984 --> 00:13:05.687 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
Oh, well, this is my big chance

00:13:05.853 --> 00:13:08.922 position:5% line:83% align:start
to promote the Fief of Morteln's
special wares, anyway.

00:13:09.223 --> 00:13:11.859 position:16% line:83% align:start
I'd like to introduce you
to my lovely fiancee,

00:13:11.992 --> 00:13:14.128 position:10% line:89% align:start
Lady Licorice Mille Hubarek.

00:13:14.261 --> 00:13:15.462 position:47% line:89% align:start
Ah!

00:13:15.597 --> 00:13:17.264 position:5% line:83% align:start
She's never attended a gathering
of southern nobles,

00:13:17.398 --> 00:13:19.634 position:7% line:89% align:start
so I asked her to accompany me.

00:13:19.768 --> 00:13:21.201 position:7% line:89% align:start
She's quite excited to be here.

00:13:21.335 --> 00:13:24.271 position:27% line:83% align:start
It is my pleasure
to make your acquaintance, sir.

00:13:24.639 --> 00:13:27.241 position:24% line:83% align:start
I am Coaton Engels,
and the pleasure is mine.

00:13:27.776 --> 00:13:30.612 position:30% line:83% align:start
Attention, all!
I wish to make an introduction.

00:13:31.145 --> 00:13:32.714 position:13% line:89% align:start
Invited here by our house,

00:13:32.846 --> 00:13:34.582 position:24% line:83% align:start
this is Lord Pastry
Mille Morteln

00:13:34.716 --> 00:13:37.017 position:7% line:89% align:start
and his fiancee, Lady Licorice!

00:13:37.786 --> 00:13:38.886 position:21% line:89% align:start
[indistinct chatter]

00:13:39.019 --> 00:13:40.454 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
Now's my big chance!

00:13:40.588 --> 00:13:42.356 position:16% line:89% align:start
I'm Pastry Mille Morteln.

00:13:42.489 --> 00:13:44.726 position:19% line:83% align:start
Despite my tender age,
I hope that everyone here

00:13:44.858 --> 00:13:46.427 position:7% line:89% align:start
will welcome me with open arms.

00:13:46.561 --> 00:13:49.196 position:19% line:89% align:start
[cheering and applause]

00:13:49.330 --> 00:13:51.700 position:21% line:83% align:start
Now, in commemoration
of our acquaintance,

00:13:51.832 --> 00:13:54.368 position:19% line:83% align:start
I've brought something
special for everybody to try.

00:13:54.502 --> 00:13:57.037 position:38% line:83% align:start
I thought
they'd go well with the tea.

00:13:57.171 --> 00:13:59.173 position:27% line:83% align:start
[MALE ATTENDEE 1]
Are they artisanal goods?

00:13:59.306 --> 00:14:01.342 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
It's called "hard candy."

00:14:01.475 --> 00:14:04.211 position:41% line:83% align:start
Candy?
So, it's something we can eat?

00:14:04.612 --> 00:14:06.980 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
By all means, help yourselves!

00:14:07.481 --> 00:14:08.482 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm!

00:14:12.119 --> 00:14:14.723 position:19% line:89% align:start
Oh! Wow! It's so good!

00:14:14.855 --> 00:14:16.323 position:10% line:89% align:start
It just melts in your mouth!

00:14:16.457 --> 00:14:20.127 position:5% line:83% align:start
It's like a warm ray of sunshine
is dancing on my tongue!

00:14:20.528 --> 00:14:21.328 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh!

00:14:21.462 --> 00:14:24.031 position:7% line:89% align:start
You should try one, Sir Coaton.

00:14:24.164 --> 00:14:25.999 position:7% line:89% align:start
You don't have to twist my arm!

00:14:28.001 --> 00:14:29.203 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:14:29.336 --> 00:14:31.238 position:38% line:83% align:start
My word!
[laughter]

00:14:31.372 --> 00:14:33.775 position:21% line:83% align:start
I'm being swept away
by a flood of sweetness!

00:14:33.907 --> 00:14:35.209 position:21% line:89% align:start
And what's this deep,

00:14:35.342 --> 00:14:37.444 position:24% line:83% align:start
rich flavor lurking
in its golden depths?

00:14:37.679 --> 00:14:41.415 position:19% line:83% align:start
The sweet, gentle aroma
is filling me with pure joy!

00:14:42.015 --> 00:14:43.183 position:41% line:89% align:start
[sips]

00:14:43.651 --> 00:14:45.085 position:13% line:89% align:start
It goes well with the tea.

00:14:45.219 --> 00:14:48.021 position:5% line:83% align:start
Truly, the sweets and tea leaves
mingle upon the tongue

00:14:48.155 --> 00:14:49.423 position:24% line:89% align:start
in perfect harmony.

00:14:49.557 --> 00:14:50.725 position:44% line:89% align:start
Nice.

00:14:50.859 --> 00:14:52.694 position:24% line:83% align:start
I didn't expect you
to be such a poet, though.

00:14:52.827 --> 00:14:54.128 position:44% line:89% align:start
Mmm!

00:14:54.261 --> 00:14:56.230 position:33% line:83% align:start
It brings out
the flavor of the tea perfectly!

00:14:56.363 --> 00:14:59.199 position:13% line:83% align:start
We made a number of samples
to send with all of you.

00:14:59.333 --> 00:15:02.069 position:19% line:83% align:start
Now that we've all met
and become friends today,

00:15:02.202 --> 00:15:04.371 position:5% line:83% align:start
if you'd like, I can easily send
some more to you

00:15:04.506 --> 00:15:06.273 position:7% line:89% align:start
by way of traveling merchants!

00:15:06.541 --> 00:15:07.842 position:27% line:83% align:start
[MALE ATTENDEE 2]
You would do that?

00:15:07.975 --> 00:15:09.243 position:13% line:89% align:start
And at no cost, of course,

00:15:09.376 --> 00:15:11.078 position:35% line:83% align:start
seeing how
they're my gift to you.

00:15:11.211 --> 00:15:12.814 position:24% line:83% align:start
[FEMALE ATTENDEE 1]
You want to gift them to us?

00:15:13.247 --> 00:15:15.015 position:30% line:89% align:start
Yes, although,

00:15:15.482 --> 00:15:17.384 position:16% line:83% align:start
[PAS] if that's the case,
I would prefer to avoid

00:15:17.519 --> 00:15:19.987 position:30% line:83% align:start
being subjected
to a tax on sugar products,

00:15:20.120 --> 00:15:22.489 position:27% line:83% align:start
even if it's just
for the merchants in question.

00:15:23.023 --> 00:15:24.491 position:27% line:89% align:start
A tax exemption?

00:15:24.626 --> 00:15:27.327 position:19% line:83% align:start
Sugary goods are taxed
very highly, as you must know.

00:15:27.461 --> 00:15:29.229 position:24% line:83% align:start
And if we consider
the small quantities

00:15:29.363 --> 00:15:31.699 position:24% line:83% align:start
and high frequency
of these hypothetical shipments,

00:15:31.833 --> 00:15:34.134 position:7% line:83% align:start
it would place an undue burden
on the merchants.

00:15:34.268 --> 00:15:36.370 position:27% line:83% align:start
[MALE ATTENDEE 1]
Well, it would seem a bit odd

00:15:36.504 --> 00:15:39.774 position:16% line:83% align:start
to apply taxes to a gift,
especially in this situation.

00:15:39.908 --> 00:15:40.875 position:27% line:83% align:start
[MALE ATTENDEE 2]
Good point.

00:15:41.008 --> 00:15:42.309 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chuckles]

00:15:42.443 --> 00:15:44.411 position:41% line:83% align:start
[RETES]
What an interesting proposal.

00:15:44.546 --> 00:15:45.279 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:15:45.412 --> 00:15:47.448 position:19% line:89% align:start
[footsteps approaching]

00:15:47.582 --> 00:15:50.752 position:21% line:83% align:start
I can't wait to hear
more about it, Lord Pastry.

00:15:51.151 --> 00:15:53.220 position:21% line:83% align:start
Thank you for coming
to my tea tasting party.

00:15:53.353 --> 00:15:55.222 position:21% line:89% align:start
Oh, Your Excellency.

00:15:55.523 --> 00:15:57.191 position:10% line:89% align:start
I was honored to be invited.

00:15:57.324 --> 00:16:00.360 position:30% line:83% align:start
And this vision
must be your lovely fiancee.

00:16:00.494 --> 00:16:01.495 position:47% line:89% align:start
Ah!

00:16:01.629 --> 00:16:04.031 position:35% line:83% align:start
It is truly
a pleasure to meet you!

00:16:04.498 --> 00:16:05.733 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm.

00:16:05.867 --> 00:16:07.367 position:7% line:89% align:start
I'd love to continue discussing

00:16:07.502 --> 00:16:09.303 position:19% line:83% align:start
what you were proposing
just now.

00:16:09.436 --> 00:16:10.738 position:19% line:89% align:start
I'm sure you understand

00:16:10.872 --> 00:16:12.707 position:19% line:83% align:start
that I prefer that any
and all business matters

00:16:12.841 --> 00:16:13.842 position:21% line:89% align:start
go through me first.

00:16:13.974 --> 00:16:15.275 position:27% line:89% align:start
Of course, I do.

00:16:15.409 --> 00:16:17.411 position:21% line:83% align:start
We're merely talking
about personal gifts.

00:16:17.946 --> 00:16:19.781 position:13% line:89% align:start
Shall we speak in private?

00:16:20.113 --> 00:16:21.415 position:33% line:89% align:start
I'd love to.

00:16:22.449 --> 00:16:23.518 position:38% line:89% align:start
Perfect.

00:16:23.651 --> 00:16:25.052 position:13% line:83% align:start
Would the lady care to wait
for us here

00:16:25.185 --> 00:16:26.420 position:19% line:89% align:start
in the meantime, then?

00:16:26.554 --> 00:16:27.522 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:16:28.121 --> 00:16:29.757 position:10% line:89% align:start
It's concerning negotiations

00:16:29.891 --> 00:16:33.227 position:21% line:83% align:start
between my household
and House Morteln, after all.

00:16:34.863 --> 00:16:36.430 position:35% line:89% align:start
Now Coaton,

00:16:36.564 --> 00:16:38.398 position:7% line:83% align:start
I trust that you will see to it
that our guests are happy.

00:16:38.533 --> 00:16:39.466 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yes.

00:16:40.234 --> 00:16:43.270 position:19% line:83% align:start
-I should be back soon.
-I understand.

00:16:44.204 --> 00:16:45.472 position:27% line:89% align:start
[LICORICE grunts]

00:16:46.941 --> 00:16:48.710 position:10% line:89% align:start
Everything will be just fine.

00:16:49.176 --> 00:16:51.144 position:24% line:83% align:start
Please, look after
Licorice for me.

00:16:51.278 --> 00:16:52.346 position:33% line:89% align:start
Will do, Pas.

00:16:52.479 --> 00:16:54.281 position:16% line:89% align:start
She's in good hands here.

00:16:55.717 --> 00:16:57.084 position:44% line:89% align:start
Oh...

00:17:02.022 --> 00:17:04.391 position:30% line:83% align:start
This is a very
intimidating room!

00:17:04.726 --> 00:17:07.461 position:10% line:83% align:start
I am the leader of the County
of Retes, after all.

00:17:07.595 --> 00:17:08.596 position:35% line:89% align:start
Do you feel

00:17:08.730 --> 00:17:10.230 position:16% line:83% align:start
I mean to bring you harm,
Your Ladyship?

00:17:10.364 --> 00:17:11.699 position:30% line:89% align:start
Of course, not.

00:17:11.833 --> 00:17:13.133 position:21% line:83% align:start
If I felt threatened,
I would have prepared

00:17:13.267 --> 00:17:14.602 position:10% line:89% align:start
ten times the number of men.

00:17:14.736 --> 00:17:17.037 position:24% line:83% align:start
A handful of guards
doesn't amount to much

00:17:17.170 --> 00:17:19.373 position:24% line:83% align:start
when your opponent
can use magic, though.

00:17:19.507 --> 00:17:22.010 position:27% line:83% align:start
